  "local_port": 35272,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I get a OBC NCL Certificate?",
  "response": "To obtain an OBC (Other Backward Classes) Non-Creamy Layer (NCL) Certificate, you need to follow these steps:\n\n### 1. **Check Eligibility:**\n   - Ensure that you belong to one of the OBC communities listed by the Central or State Government.\n   - Verify that your family's income falls within the non-creamy layer limits, which is currently set at less than \u20b98 lakh per annum.\n\n### 2. **Gather Required Documents:**\n   - Proof of identity (Aadhaar Card, Voter ID, etc.)\n   - Proof of address (Aadhaar Card, Voter ID, utility bills, etc.)\n   - Proof of caste (community certificate issued by a competent authority)\n   - Income certificate of parents/guardian (from the relevant authority)\n   - Affidavit stating that you belong to the OBC category and that your family's income is within the non-creamy layer limits\n   - Recent passport-sized photographs\n\n### 3. **Application Process:**\n   - **Offline Method:**\n     - Visit the office of the Tehsildar, Revenue Officer, or any other designated authority in your area.\n     - Obtain the application form for the OBC NCL Certificate.\n     - Fill out the form with the required details and attach the necessary documents.\n     - Submit the form to the issuing authority.\n   \n   - **Online Method:**\n     - Visit the official website of your state government where the service is offered (e.g., for Maharashtra, it's the Aaple Sarkar portal).\n     - Register and log in to the portal.\n     - Fill out the online application form for the OBC NCL Certificate.\n     - Upload the required documents as specified.\n     - Pay any applicable fees and submit the application.\n\n### 4. **Verification and Issuance:**\n   - The issuing authority will verify your documents and application details.\n   - Once verified, the OBC NCL Certificate will be issued.\n   - If you applied online, the certificate may be sent to you via email or made available for download on the portal.\n   - For offline applications, you may need to collect the certificate in person or it will be mailed to your address.\n\n### 5. **Validity:**\n   - The OBC NCL Certificate is generally valid for one year from the date of issue.\n   - You may need to renew it annually if required for educational or employment purposes.\n\n### Additional Tips:\n   - Always check the specific requirements and procedures of your state or union territory, as they might vary slightly.\n   - Keep copies of all submitted documents and the certificate for future reference.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to obtain your OBC NCL Certificate. If you encounter any issues, consider reaching out to the issuing authority or a local helpdesk for assistance.",
